{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":16462,"name":"Rico Decho","username":"rico.decho","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rico.decho/{size}/239_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-08T10:24:10.450Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe 1.0 version of the Crack language has just been released !!!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://crack-lang.blogspot.be\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://crack-lang.blogspot.be\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://www.mindhog.net/~mmuller/projects/crack/Manual-1.0.html\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://www.mindhog.net/~mmuller/projects/crack/Manual-1.0.html\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFeatures :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInfluences : C, C++, Java, Python\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSyntax : C-style, curly-brace\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTyping : Static, strong (with some implicit conversion)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompiler : native compiled, either JIT (at runtime) or AOT (native binary)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eParadigms :  Object oriented, procedural\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGarbage Collection : Reference counted objects, programmer controlled\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOO Features : Virtual functions, overloaded functions, multiple inheritance, generics.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAwesome !!!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIMHO, it could be the \u003cstrong\u003ePERFECT C#-LIKE SCRIPTING LANGUAGE FOR URHO3D\u003c/strong\u003e, much better than AngelScript or Lua…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAt the moment, it only runs on \u003cstrong\u003eLinux\u003c/strong\u003e, and I need a FFI example to make some tests.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut LLVM is portable and can generate ARM machine language, and I’ve already asked to Michael to explain us how to use Crack from a host application.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-08T11:06:57.033Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":231,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":1163.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2868,"topic_slug":"crack-scripting-language","display_username":"Rico Decho","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://crack-lang.blogspot.be","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Crack Language News","clicks":65},{"url":"http://www.mindhog.net/~mmuller/projects/crack/Manual-1.0.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"The Crack Programming Language Guide","clicks":28}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":682,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16464,"name":"","username":"TheSHEEEP","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/thesheeep/{size}/74_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-08T11:20:39.731Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOh, look. Another scripting language… \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=5\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI don’t want to be too negative, but if it does not have strong IDE support, I think the valid use cases will be fairly limited. And not being cross-platform makes it dead in the water, to be blunt.\u003cbr\u003e\nThe syntax itself looks nice. Except the `. Good luck with that symbol on non-US keyboards (it is left of backspace on Finnish and German keyboards, for example, and requires shift pressed. Ugh).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, I agree that both AngelScript and Lua have that problem as well (no great IDE with autocompletion…) and so far, I think C#/Mono is the only scripting language that allows you to do proper coding when using a scripting language.\u003cbr\u003e\nWhat I’ll do for my project is completely ignoring the scripting present in Urho and rolling my own with C# so I can get autocompletion in IDEs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen I chose the scripting language to use, my checkpoints were:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePerformance\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eJIT-support (when developing, scripting languages without this lose a lot of a appeal if you can’t reload a script at runtime)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEase of use (for scripters/modders)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVersatility (Lua for example, is extremely limited without many addons, there isn’t even a proper socket API)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEase of integration (for coders)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe only downside of C#/Mono is that it is horrible to integrate/embed and that part is hilariously bad documented. It is of course easy to run some C# script from C++, but any real use case requires interfaces between the two layers and that is just a nightmare with Mono. But on the upside, you only have to do that integration step once.\u003cbr\u003e\nAlso, JIT/script reload at runtime is hard to do with it (but not impossible).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn former projects, I usually went with Lua, but the lack of automatic autocompletion and the fact that its syntax is simply weird as hell and no modder really likes it made me drop it.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-08T11:34:41.352Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":42,"readers_count":41,"score":33.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2868,"topic_slug":"crack-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":513,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16465,"name":"","username":"slapin","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/dfb087/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-03-08T11:41:53.447Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAh, another one of these llvm stuff \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/frowning.png?v=5\" title=\":frowning:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":frowning:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-08T11:41:53.447Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":39,"readers_count":38,"score":12.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2868,"topic_slug":"crack-scripting-language","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"TheSHEEEP","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/thesheeep/{size}/74_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":554,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16472,"name":"Rico Decho","username":"rico.decho","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rico.decho/{size}/239_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-08T13:10:07.364Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThat’s right.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt’s not ready as a viable alternative to Angelscript now.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut to me, it’s actually “Angelscript done right”.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThus my post…\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-08T13:10:07.364Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":37,"readers_count":36,"score":17.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2868,"topic_slug":"crack-scripting-language","display_username":"Rico Decho","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":682,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16480,"name":"Justin Miller","username":"jmiller","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jmiller/{size}/2367_2.png","created_at":"2017-03-08T18:55:34.841Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"2868\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/thesheeep/40/74_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e TheSHEEEP:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, I agree that both AngelScript and Lua have that problem as well (no great IDE with autocompletion…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIncluding \u003cstrong\u003eAngelScriptAPI.h\u003c/strong\u003e in search paths has been the usual solution. I’d assume it should work somewhat consistently across IDEs, if not ideal.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/configuring-codelite-for-editing-as-scripts/68\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003eAutocomplete and syntax highlighting in CodeLite\u003c/a\u003e – which I find to be a great IDE; ofc that’s subjective. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=5\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-08T18:55:34.841Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":36,"readers_count":35,"score":32.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":2868,"topic_slug":"crack-scripting-language","display_username":"Justin Miller","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/configuring-codelite-for-editing-as-scripts/68","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Configuring CodeLite for editing *.as scripts","clicks":13}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"username":"TheSHEEEP","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/thesheeep/{size}/74_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":21,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":16481,"name":"","username":"slapin","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/dfb087/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-03-08T19:23:10.453Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThere’s no great IDEs except for vim!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-03-08T19:23:10.453Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":35,"readers_count":34,"score":7.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2868,"topic_slug":"crack-scripting-language","display_username":"","prim